/*Problem Statement
As a New Year's gift, Dolphin received a string s of length 19.
The string s has the following format: 
[five lowercase English letters],[seven lowercase English letters],[five lowercase English letters].
Dolphin wants to convert the comma-separated string s into a space-separated string.
Write a program to perform the conversion for him.

Constraints
The length of s is 19.
The sixth and fourteenth characters in s are ,.
The other characters in s are lowercase English letters.*/
#include<stdio.h>
#include<string.h>

int main()
{
    char S[20], s1[6], s2[8], s3[6];

    do
    {
        scanf("%s", S);
    } while (strlen(S)!=19);

    int i=0;
    while(S[i]!=',')
    {
        s1[i]=S[i];
        i++;
    };
    s1[i] = '\0';
    int j=i+1,k=0;
    while(S[j]!=',')
    {
        s2[k]=S[j];
        j++;
        k++;
    };
    s2[k] = '\0';
    int m=j+1,n=0;
    while(S[m]!='\0')
    {
        s3[n]=S[m];
        n++;
        m++;
    };
    s3[n] = '\0';
    printf("%s %s %s", s1, s2, s3);

    return 0;

}